1.What is CRM? Salesforce CRM CRM stands for Customer Relationship Management. It is a system used by companies to:
 •Store customer information
 •Track sales and customer interactions
 •Manage leads and opportunities
 •Improve customer service
 •Increase business growth
2.Why Companies Use Salesforce?
  
 Salesforce￼ Companies use Salesforce because it helps them:

 •Manage customer data All customer details are stored in one place.
 •Track sales activities Sales teams can monitor leads, opportunities, and deals.
 •Improve customer service Support teams can quickly solve customer issues.
 •Automate business processes Tasks like emails, approvals, and reminders can be automated.
 •Generate reports and dashboards Managers can analyze business performance easily.
 •Work from anywhere Salesforce is cloud-based, so it can be accessed online
3.Account An Account means a company or organization with which we do business. Example: If your company is dealing with Infosys, then Infosys is an Account.

 •Company name
 •Address
 •Phone number
 •Industry type
Contact A Contact means a person working in that company. Example: If “Rahul Sharma” works in Infosys and communicates with your company, then Rahul Sharma is a Contact.

 •Person name
 •Email
 •Phone number
 •Job role
Opportunity An Opportunity means a possible business deal or sale. Example: If Infosys is planning to buy software from your company, that sales deal is called an Opportunity.

 •Deal amount
 •Deal stage
 •Expected closing date
   
